From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0067/N] metaspace: 9 more BytesPerWord -> sizeof(MetaWord) sites

Follow-up to patch 0065. The static seam scan (scripts/scan_cheri_seams.py,
docs/10) enumerated all `word_count * BytesPerWord` sites in HotSpot.
Patch 0065 fixed 9 sites in the metaspace subsystem; this patch fixes
the remaining 8 distinct sites (9 edits, one file had 2):

  - classLoaderMetaspace.cpp:103  delta_capacity_until_GC arg
  - metaspace.cpp:981             CDS dump alignment check
                                  (this line was MISSED by 0065 due
                                   to a typo in the python apply script)
  - commitMask.cpp:63,65,82       3 commit-granule alignment asserts
  - metachunk.cpp:237,240         2 buddy-chunk Sanity asserts
  - metaspaceCommon.cpp:180       MIN block byte_size MAX2 floor
  - testHelpers.cpp:74            unit test ReservedSpace sizing

Most are alignment ASSERTs that only fire in debug builds or under
specific paths (CDS, buddy splitting). Only 3 are on the hot
allocation path:

  - delta_capacity_until_GC: undersizes GC threshold by 2x on CHERI
    (effectively makes Metaspace GC fire 2x sooner than intended;
    correctness-affecting but not crashing)
  - MetaspaceCommon::get_raw_word_size MAX2 floor: MinWordSize *
    BytesPerWord was used as the byte-size floor for deallocated
    blocks. With MinWordSize=2 the floor was 16 bytes; now 32. This
    matters because the BinList block layout includes capability
    members and the actual minimum is 32 bytes on CHERI.

Empirical: build clean, JVM still crashes at memset+0x16b after 13
bootclasses (same point as before 0067). These fixes are necessary
correctness changes but not load-bearing for the current crash.
Committed as part of systematic seam-fixing rather than crash-driven
fixes.

Pairs with: scripts/scan_cheri_seams.py + docs/10_cheri_seam_scan.md
            which produced the worklist.

Refs: docs/10_cheri_seam_scan.md (Category A in memory subsystem)

